    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.37a.24"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">24</fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        111 Carson Drive 
                        Monroeville, Pennsylvania 15146
                        May 21, 1973
                    </dateline>
                    
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Skyrim <hi rend="caps">R.D.</hi> 7</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Columbia, Missouri 65201</addrLine>
                    </address>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Dr. Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I am a doctoral student of American Literature at the University of Pittsburgh. I began to read your works after I saw your interviews with Dick Cavett. This spring my dissertation committee accepted the prospectus for my dissertation, tentatively titled "A Thematic Study of the Works of John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt." In preparing the prospectus I have read all your works except the two novels and certain newspaper reviews which I have not been able to locate so far.</p>
                
                <p>Would you consent to correspond with me during the following months so that I might verify certain points of interpretation and biography with you? I would like especially to talk to you about your early short stories. I rejoice in my choice of your works as my dissertation subject, but I would feel on much firmer critical ground if I could clarify some questions I have.</p> 
                <closer>
                    <salute>Sincerely,</salute>
                    
                    <signed>Linda D. DeLowry</signed>
                    <signed>(Miss) Linda D. DeLowry</signed>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
